'''''Inhale Yoga with Steve Ross''''', sometimes shortened to just ''Inhale'', was an [[Oxygen Network]] television show in the USA that was shown at 6am from spring 2000 until spring 2010.<ref name="bib">{{cite web|url=http://www.bringinhaleback.org/|title=Bring Inhale Back|accessdate=12 November 2010}}</ref> The show featured the yoga instructor Steve Ross, named the "guru of Los Angeles" by ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''.<ref name="maha">{{cite web|url=http://www.mahayoga.com/|title=Maha Yoga|publisher=Maha Yoga|accessdate=12 November 2010}}</ref> ''Inhale'' is lauded by fans for the groovy music, high energy pace and wry jokes by Ross. <ref name="bbmom">{{cite web|url=http://www.bradybunchmom.com/2009/04/inhale-with-steve-ross.html|title=Inhale with Steve Ross|date=23 April 2009|work=Brady Bunch Mom|accessdate=12 November 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101007065726/http://www.bradybunchmom.com/2009/04/inhale-with-steve-ross.html|archivedate=7 October 2010|df=}}</ref> Critics note the lack of technical guidance and disruptive commercial breaks.<ref name="bully">{{cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/id/2076431/|title=The Sun Salutation King: Oxygen's yoga bully.|last=Heffernan|first=Virginia|date=7 January 2003|work=Slate|accessdate=12 November 2010}}</ref> Ross currently{{when|date=January 2015}} has his own studio called Maha Yoga in Los Angeles.<ref name="maha"/>
