{{Infobox person |name = Jean-Paul Audet |image = |alt = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date|1918|12|07}} |birth_place = |death_date = {{Death date and age|1993|11|12|1918|12|07}} |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = |nationality = |awards = [[Order of Canada]] }} '''Jean-Paul Audet''', {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|OC|FRSC}} (December 7, 1918 &ndash; November 12, 1993) was a [[French Canadian]] academic and philosopher.
He was a professor and former head of the [[Université de Montréal]]'s Department of Philosophy.
In 1988, he was made an Officer of the [[Order of Canada]] for his "contribution to the field of theology".[http://www.gg.ca/honours/search-recherche/honours-desc.asp?lang=e&TypeID=orc&id=625] In 1969, he was awarded the [[Molson Prize]]. In 1970, he was made a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Canada]].
