{{Augustine}}
'''''Our Lord's Sermon on the Mount''''' is a book by the 4th–5th-century saint [[Augustine of Hippo]].<ref name=Lancel >''Saint Augustine'' by Serge Lancel, 2010, {{ISBN|0-334-02866-3}}, p. 177</ref>

Augustine undertook this work before working on the [[Pauline Epistles]] because he considered chapters 5–7 of the [[Gospel of Matthew]] (the [[Sermon on the Mount]]) "a perfect standard of the Christian life".<ref name=Lancel />

