{{Ismailism|collapsed=1}}
With the exception of the [[Mustaali]] and [[Nizari]] Ismaili{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}, most of other [[Ismaili]] [[Shi'a]] [[Muslims]] believe in [[panentheism]], meaning God is both [[reality]] and transcendent of it. While the figure of the [[Deity|Godhead]] is beyond this universe, the Godhead has created reality, which is the [[Imamah (Shi'a Ismaili doctrine)|Imam]] himself. All living beings exist in this reality, and to understand the Imam is to understand reality and truth and thereby gain salvation.

